	<h1>Activation Context (2)</h1>
	
	Look at the URL of this page. It is the page render request. You can see the <strong>activation context</strong> at the end.<br/>
	To receive the activation context, a page must have an <strong>onActivate(..)</strong> method with the right number and 
	type of parameters.<br/><br/>
	
	This page has been activated with context <em>${personId}</em>. Here is that Person:<br/>

	<div class="eg">
		<t:beandisplay object="person">[BeanDisplay here]</t:beandisplay>
	</div>

	References:	
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/5.3/apidocs/org/apache/tapestry5/corelib/components/PageLink.html">PageLink</a>, 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/page-navigation.html">Page Navigation</a>, 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/component-rendering.html">Component Rendering</a>.<br/><br/>

	<t:pagelink t:page="examples/navigation/ActivationContext1">Return</t:pagelink><br/><br/>
	<t:pagelink t:page="Index">Home</t:pagelink><br/><br/>

